Well, hello there. Come on.
Come, come, come. Have you a seat.

02:01.920 --> 02:03.729
Kick them shoes off you.

02:04.360 --> 02:07.682
Shh. But not too loud, now.

02:10.400 --> 02:13.609
You see, me, I'm fixing to have me
some gumbo tonight.

02:13.760 --> 02:16.843
And them catfish
can get mighty skittish, yeah.

02:17.000 --> 02:18.843
Whoa. Whoa.

02:19.000 --> 02:21.287
What...? Oh, no, you don't.
You get back, you!

02:21.440 --> 02:22.965
Get back, y'all loony lizards!

02:23.120 --> 02:25.964
I'm going to have y'all for my gumbo.

02:34.440 --> 02:35.680
Oh, what...?

02:35.840 --> 02:37.205
[LAUGHS]

02:37.360 --> 02:39.601
Oh, that's a leech.

02:39.760 --> 02:43.890
Oh, you cute little critter.
Yeah, yeah, that's right.

02:45.440 --> 02:46.441
[GULPS]

02:46.600 --> 02:48.090
[ANIMAL SCREECHING NEARBY]

02:48.680 --> 02:50.808
You know what that was?

02:51.040 --> 02:53.042
Me neither. Hoo-hoo!

02:53.200 --> 02:56.363
But it could be one of them vampires.

02:56.520 --> 02:58.443
They all around these parts, yeah.

02:59.240 --> 03:00.526
Look here.

03:01.800 --> 03:04.371
That's the jewels
of a vampire bride, y'all.

03:04.520 --> 03:06.124
I found them down the bayou.

03:06.280 --> 03:07.884
They're some kind of pretty, eh?

03:08.040 --> 03:11.567
But let me tell y'all, she didn't
wanna get married to no vampire, no.

03:11.720 --> 03:13.688
And who can blame her? Who would?

03:13.840 --> 03:15.410
But she was forced to.

03:15.560 --> 03:18.404
And then came a talking dog...

03:18.560 --> 03:21.325
Whoop. I done almost spoiled the ending.
Heh.

03:21.480 --> 03:23.767
We got to start at the beginning, cher.

03:23.920 --> 03:29.051
And that,
that happened along way from here.

03:49.840 --> 03:52.605
VELMA [OVER RADIO]: <i>Scooby, Shaggy,
you guys spot anything yet?</i>

03:52.760 --> 03:55.331
- Uh-uh.
- Call me crazy, Scooby...

03:55.480 --> 03:58.324
- ...but don't these pipes look familiar?
- Kind of.

03:58.480 --> 04:01.131
SHAGGY: Didn't we run into
that big rat creature down here?

04:01.280 --> 04:04.682
That was two weeks ago, Shaggy,
in the New York sewers.

04:05.120 --> 04:06.451
How could you forget?

04:06.600 --> 04:08.682
Wasn't that the glop monster?

04:09.160 --> 04:12.369
The glop monster was on Saturday.
Remember?

04:12.520 --> 04:16.684
Rat creature, then glop monster,
then snake-osaurus.

04:17.279 --> 04:19.089
They're all starting to merge.

04:19.240 --> 04:21.971
Better get ready for this one, Shaggy,
because it's coming.

04:22.320 --> 04:24.846
I know. It's coming our way.

04:25.000 --> 04:26.729
That was on Saturday too.

04:27.240 --> 04:28.480
[WHIMPERS]

04:29.200 --> 04:30.770
[HOWLING]

04:31.560 --> 04:33.005
SCOOBY:
Huh?

04:33.480 --> 04:35.084
[WHIMPERS]

04:35.240 --> 04:37.242
[YELLS THEN GRUNTS]

04:37.840 --> 04:39.569
[SCREECHES]

04:39.960 --> 04:41.007
[WHIMPERS]

04:41.600 --> 04:43.568
[SHAGGY & SCOOBY SCREAM]

04:43.720 --> 04:45.643
- Hang on.
SHAGGY: It's huge!

04:45.800 --> 04:47.131
We're coming.

04:47.640 --> 04:50.849
Whatever you do, don't let it eat you
before we get there.

04:51.000 --> 04:52.445
[SHAGGY & SCOOBY WHIMPERING]

04:55.240 --> 04:57.004
[SQUEAKING]

04:57.640 --> 05:00.041
Oh, it's just a common cockroach.

05:00.200 --> 05:02.771
There is nothing common
about a cockroach.

05:04.200 --> 05:06.123
Is it singing?

05:06.480 --> 05:08.687
Not singing. Signaling.

05:08.840 --> 05:10.444
Signaling to what?

05:10.840 --> 05:12.604
To that cockroach.

05:12.760 --> 05:14.125
[SCREECHING]

05:14.280 --> 05:16.123
[BOTH SCREAM]

05:17.480 --> 05:18.527
DAPHNE:
Gross!

05:18.920 --> 05:21.241
Glad I brought a giant roll of flypaper.

05:22.200 --> 05:24.362
Oh... Unh!

05:24.520 --> 05:25.885
[FRED MUMBLING]

05:31.800 --> 05:33.450
There, that's better.

05:33.600 --> 05:34.726
Or not.

05:45.400 --> 05:46.845
[GRUNTS]

05:49.280 --> 05:50.441
[GROANS]

05:50.600 --> 05:52.329
VELMA:
Mr. Clapper.

05:52.480 --> 05:55.165
Of course.
He was using the cockroach monster...

05:55.320 --> 05:58.164
...to drum up customers
for his exterminator company.

05:58.320 --> 06:01.642
Just as I thought, guys. Guys?

06:02.120 --> 06:04.043
[SCOOBY WHIMPERS]

06:06.600 --> 06:09.001
[FRED GRUNTING]

06:10.440 --> 06:11.680
[SQUEAKING]

06:11.840 --> 06:13.763
Ew! Get it away!

06:14.560 --> 06:17.086
I think we could all use a nice vacation.

06:17.840 --> 06:19.285
Vacation?

06:21.120 --> 06:24.920
FRED: No, Daphne.
SHAGGY: Don't do it. We're begging you.

06:25.480 --> 06:27.767
DAPHNE:
I'm sorry, guys, but I have to do this.

06:27.920 --> 06:30.605
SHAGGY: No!
SCOOBY: No!

06:30.880 --> 06:32.405
Show tunes make road trips
so much better.

06:32.560 --> 06:34.050
[UPBEAT SHOW TUNE
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

06:34.200 --> 06:35.565
The songs do get stuck in your head.

06:35.720 --> 06:36.926
Tell us about it.

06:37.080 --> 06:38.650
[BOTH GRUNTING]

06:38.800 --> 06:40.484
Well, I don't hear Velma complaining.

06:40.640 --> 06:42.210
Did you say something?

06:42.360 --> 06:44.362
Oh, are we still listening to show tunes?

06:44.520 --> 06:48.047
You all complain now, but I bet
you'll be singing along in no time.

06:48.520 --> 06:51.285
SHAGGY: Ha, ha. You hear that, Scoob?
SCOOBY: Yeah.

06:51.440 --> 06:53.329
[SCOOBY LAUGHS]

06:53.480 --> 06:57.280
So, Velma, you ever gonna reveal
our secret vacation destination?

06:57.440 --> 06:58.771
Not till we get there.

06:59.120 --> 07:00.360
You guys are gonna love it.

07:00.680 --> 07:03.081
Just as long as
they've got plenty of sunshine.

07:03.240 --> 07:08.201
There is only one thing Scooby-Doo
and I are hoping for this vacation.

07:08.360 --> 07:12.206
[SINGING] <i>♪ I don't want no more ghouls
♪ Or nothing scary</i>

07:12.880 --> 07:16.282
<i>♪ No apparitions giving me a fright</i>

07:17.720 --> 07:21.805
<i>♪ Don't want nothing
that I need to bury</i>

07:21.960 --> 07:24.930
<i>♪ Or creatures that go
bumping in the night</i>

07:25.080 --> 07:26.241
[BOTH LAUGH]

07:26.400 --> 07:30.803
DAPHNE: <i>♪ No poltergeists
and nothing supernatural</i>

07:30.960 --> 07:33.645
<i>♪ No giant beast
♪ That sneaks up from behind</i>

07:33.800 --> 07:35.245
[BOTH LAUGH]

07:35.400 --> 07:37.528
<i>♪ No ghosts that rattle chains</i>

07:37.680 --> 07:39.808
<i>♪ Or things that eat your brains</i>

07:39.960 --> 07:44.010
<i>♪ No banshee witch
♪ That scares me out of my mind</i>

07:44.400 --> 07:46.880
<i>♪ We're finally on vacation</i>

07:47.040 --> 07:48.644
<i>♪ And going someplace new</i>

07:49.000 --> 07:51.082
SCOOBY:
<i>♪ Rest and relaxation</i>

07:51.240 --> 07:52.685
ALL:
<i>♪ Is all we're gonna do</i>

07:52.840 --> 07:55.571
FRED:
<i>♪ I don't want no zombies or kooks</i>

07:55.720 --> 07:57.290
<i>♪ My friends, we're finally done</i>

07:57.440 --> 08:00.125
<i>♪ With all them goblins and spooks</i>

08:00.280 --> 08:01.964
<i>♪ That kept us on the run</i>

08:02.120 --> 08:04.566
<i>♪ We're gonna be cool as cukes</i>

08:04.720 --> 08:06.848
<i>♪ Our monster days are through</i>

08:07.040 --> 08:10.362
<i>♪ - No demonic beast and nothing
deceased</i> SCOOBY: <i>♪ It's time to relax</i>

08:10.520 --> 08:12.010
SHAGGY:
<i>♪ And that's what we're gonna do</i>

08:12.160 --> 08:14.845
[ALL SCATTING]

08:20.880 --> 08:24.965
VELMA: <I>♪ No more frown
♪ We're moving down the road now

08:25.400 --> 08:28.210
<i>♪ Keep that metal pedal to the floor</i>

08:29.440 --> 08:33.808
<i>♪ We haven't got a clue
♪ Where we're headed to</i>

08:33.960 --> 08:37.282
ALL: <I>♪ But it's somewhere
♪ That we've never been before

08:38.880 --> 08:41.008
DAPHNE & VELMA:
<i>♪ Cruising down the highway</i>

08:41.159 --> 08:43.207
<i>♪ Free without a care</i>

08:43.360 --> 08:46.887
<i>♪ It feels bizarre because
♪ There are no werewolves anywhere</i>

08:47.040 --> 08:49.646
<i>♪ Don't want no dragons or freaks</i>

08:49.800 --> 08:51.404
<i>♪ And no crazy evil sprites</i>

08:51.560 --> 08:54.530
<i>♪ I don't want no
phantom that shrieks</i>

08:54.680 --> 08:55.886
<i>♪ Haunting us every night</i>

08:56.040 --> 08:59.044
<i>♪ I don't want no Comic-Con geeks</i>

08:59.200 --> 09:01.009
<i>♪ Walking up out of the blue</i>

09:01.440 --> 09:03.568
DAPHNE & VELMA:
<i>♪ Dressed like bats and 7-fool rats</i>

09:03.720 --> 09:06.200
<i>♪ Chasing me down and saying
♪ "How do you do?"</i>

09:06.360 --> 09:08.840
[ALL SCATTING]

09:14.400 --> 09:18.849
<i>♪ Lift your hand up high
♪ Let it wave goodbye</i>

09:19.000 --> 09:22.891
<i>♪ To them gremlins
and monsters galore</i>

09:23.440 --> 09:27.889
<i>♪ Tell them all we're gone
♪ 'Cause we're moving on</i>

09:28.040 --> 09:32.841
<i>♪ And we ain't coming
back any more. ♪</i>

09:33.360 --> 09:35.647
[ALL SCATTING]

09:46.400 --> 09:48.129
Hey, look, our destination.

09:48.280 --> 09:51.250
See? Show tunes really do
help pass the time.

09:51.920 --> 09:54.924
DAPHNE:
"Petit Chauve Sourie Ville"? Ooh.

09:55.080 --> 09:57.162
[DAPHNE SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

09:57.920 --> 10:00.287
Like, it sounds monster-free to me.
Hoo-hon!

10:00.440 --> 10:02.044
Yeah, up top.

10:02.440 --> 10:04.010
What does the French translate to?

10:04.160 --> 10:06.128
Oh, it means "Little Bat Town."

10:06.280 --> 10:08.681
- Uh-oh.
- Not to worry, Scoob.

10:08.840 --> 10:12.686
Velma promised us this place would be
ghost-, ghoul-, and goblin-free.

10:14.200 --> 10:15.201
What? Whoa!

10:16.240 --> 10:17.321
[BOTH SCREAM]

10:17.480 --> 10:18.720
[TIRES SCREECH]

10:18.880 --> 10:19.881
[MAN GRUNTS]

10:20.800 --> 10:21.801
[VELMA & FRED GASP]

10:21.960 --> 10:23.246
[BOTH YELL]

10:23.640 --> 10:26.450
Hey, I'm stalking here! I'm stalking here!

10:29.200 --> 10:31.202
She didn't say anything about vampires.

10:31.360 --> 10:32.361
Didn't I?

10:32.520 --> 10:33.521
[DAPHNE CHUCKLES]

10:33.680 --> 10:34.920
Mm, must've slipped my mind.

10:35.080 --> 10:36.081
[BOTH WHIMPER]

10:36.240 --> 10:38.129
Shaggy, Scooby, you can come out.

10:38.280 --> 10:39.805
It was just a kid in a costume.

10:40.360 --> 10:42.124
Like, you sure?

10:42.280 --> 10:46.126
Absolutely. He's probably just here
for the vampire festival.

10:46.400 --> 10:47.845
BOTH:
Oh.

10:48.000 --> 10:49.161
Vampire festival?

10:51.360 --> 10:54.523
VELMA:
Yup, Vampire Palooza.

10:55.720 --> 10:58.291
You brought us to a vampire convention?

10:58.440 --> 10:59.726
To relax?

10:59.880 --> 11:01.291
Not a vampire convention.

11:01.440 --> 11:04.011
It's a celebration of all things vampiric.

11:04.160 --> 11:08.210
Cool. And what better place
to experience it than Little Bat Town.

11:08.360 --> 11:12.524
Ooh! Vampires are so romantic.
Have you read <i>Silverlight</i> ?

11:13.880 --> 11:17.009
Twelve times. I'm hoping
the author will be here to sign it.

11:17.160 --> 11:19.083
Are we missing something here?

11:19.240 --> 11:23.689
Like, what's so romantic about
undead creatures who sleep in coffins...

11:23.840 --> 11:26.923
...prowl the night in search of victims,
steal their blood...

11:27.080 --> 11:29.970
...and turn them
into their zombie servants?

11:30.120 --> 11:32.248
Oh, those are old-school vampires.

11:32.400 --> 11:34.880
Modern vampires are fun and super-cool.

11:35.280 --> 11:37.601
Vampires don't sleep in coffins any more.

11:37.760 --> 11:38.886
They sleep in Seattle.

11:39.040 --> 11:40.371
[VELMA CHUCKLES]

11:40.520 --> 11:43.410
- You're not making us feel better.
- Uh-uh.

11:43.760 --> 11:46.491
Says here this place was founded
in the 19th century...

11:46.640 --> 11:50.884
...by Abraham Van Helsing, the famous
vampire hunter of Dracula fame.

11:51.200 --> 11:54.090
And it's still owned by
one of the Van Helsings' descendants.

11:54.640 --> 11:56.324
So it's like a ghost town.

11:56.680 --> 11:59.047
No, a vampire ghost town.

11:59.520 --> 12:00.931
[BOTH WHIMPER]

12:01.080 --> 12:04.448
This is the last time
we let you pick the vacation spot.

12:04.600 --> 12:06.602
- Yeah.
- Relax, guys.

12:06.760 --> 12:08.524
There's absolutely nothing to fear.

12:09.000 --> 12:11.401
Hey, Scoob,
when have we heard that before?

12:14.560 --> 12:16.608
Every day of our lives.

12:17.640 --> 12:19.085
You guys worry too much.

12:19.480 --> 12:21.721
Well, we're not the only ones.

12:22.120 --> 12:28.207
This fair is an abomination,
an affront to all that is good and decent.

12:28.360 --> 12:29.361
[CARNIVAL MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

12:29.520 --> 12:31.488
Sign the petition to ban vampires?

12:31.920 --> 12:35.083
- Like, that's a cause we can support.
- Mm-hm, mm-hm.

12:35.240 --> 12:38.050
Here there be demons.

12:38.200 --> 12:41.329
Here there also be corn dogs.

12:44.360 --> 12:46.727
Fools. Fools, I say.

12:46.880 --> 12:52.762
Will you allow temptation to lure you
into the fangy den of the bloodsucker?

12:53.160 --> 12:55.891
Pretty much. Corn dogs!

12:56.040 --> 12:57.644
Corn dogs, yum.

12:57.800 --> 12:59.086
[SHAGGY CHUCKLES]

13:01.080 --> 13:03.890
Hey, Scoob, if the food's this good
outside the festival...

13:04.040 --> 13:07.249
...I can't wait to see
what they've got inside.

13:08.480 --> 13:10.403
Guys, there's no such thing
as real vampires.

13:10.560 --> 13:11.561
SCOOBY:
Mm.

13:11.720 --> 13:14.041
No such thing
as paying customers either.

13:14.200 --> 13:15.201
[SIGHS]

13:15.360 --> 13:18.762
Five more complimentary passes.
I'll be lucky to break even this year.

13:18.920 --> 13:21.969
Like, not exactly the kind of bite
I'm looking for.

13:22.120 --> 13:23.884
[LAUGHS]

13:24.040 --> 13:26.122
We're guests of Vincent Van Helsing.

13:26.280 --> 13:27.327
- He owns...
- Yes, yes.

13:27.480 --> 13:29.448
I'm Lita Rutland, owner of the festival.

13:29.600 --> 13:32.922
I know who Van Helsing is.
Unfortunately no one else does.

13:33.960 --> 13:35.883
[GRUNTING]

13:38.280 --> 13:40.044
[SNORING]

13:42.080 --> 13:43.411
[GRUNTS]

13:44.200 --> 13:47.443
Imagine a vampire author
in these vampire-crazed times...

13:47.600 --> 13:48.965
...who doesn't sell any books.

13:49.440 --> 13:51.010
Maybe he's just having an off day.

13:51.360 --> 13:52.771
Yeah, maybe.

13:53.200 --> 13:56.044
He's still one of the foremost authorities
on vampire history.

13:56.520 --> 14:00.286
Perhaps, but the world's moved on
from his old-school vampire tales.

14:00.440 --> 14:02.602
Well, I've read all his books.

14:02.760 --> 14:03.886
I think.

14:04.280 --> 14:09.525
Well, you kids enjoy your free lunch. I
mean, your time here at Vampire Palooza.

14:09.680 --> 14:10.681
She's friendly.

14:14.120 --> 14:15.167
Velma.

14:15.640 --> 14:18.007
It's good to see a familiar face.

14:18.160 --> 14:22.085
And this must be the rest
of the famous mystery-hunting crew.

14:22.520 --> 14:24.363
Guys, I'd like you to meet our host...

14:24.800 --> 14:27.087
...the world's foremost expert
on vampires...

14:27.600 --> 14:29.170
...Vincent Van Helsing.

14:29.320 --> 14:32.642
A pleasure.
You know, I'm also an author.

14:32.800 --> 14:34.689
Perhaps you've read my books?

14:34.840 --> 14:36.968
My vampire tales are fact-based.

14:37.120 --> 14:40.806
And not that lusty teen tripe
that's all the rage these days.

14:41.240 --> 14:44.528
Yeah, that modern stuff is way lame.

14:45.000 --> 14:46.764
Hey, did you guys know
Mr. Van Helsing...

14:47.160 --> 14:50.289
...is the great-great-great-grandson
of Abraham Van Helsing?

14:50.640 --> 14:52.290
FRED:
Wow, a direct descendant...

14:52.440 --> 14:56.161
- ...of the famous vampire hunter for real?
- It's true.

14:56.320 --> 15:00.325
My family has been in the vampire
business for a long time.

15:00.480 --> 15:03.529
That's why I became a vampirologist.

15:03.680 --> 15:05.170
A vampire-what-igist?

15:05.680 --> 15:10.607
Uh, vampirology is the academic study
of the vampire from A to Z.

15:10.760 --> 15:13.001
Come, I'll show you.

15:14.600 --> 15:17.080
VAN HELSING:
My collection of vampire artifacts...

15:17.240 --> 15:20.483
...go back to the very dawn
of the vampire.

15:20.640 --> 15:22.722
FRED:
This stuff is fang-tastic.

15:23.040 --> 15:25.964
Heh. Get it?
I used the word "fang" instead of "fan."

15:26.120 --> 15:27.406
[CHUCKLES]

15:27.560 --> 15:28.607
We get it.

15:28.760 --> 15:31.923
Wow, the ancient book of vampire.

15:32.080 --> 15:34.924
I thought only one copy
of this existed in the world.

15:35.080 --> 15:36.445
You're looking at it.

15:36.880 --> 15:38.962
Check out these awesome stakes.

15:39.120 --> 15:41.600
- Steaks? Where?
- Yummy.

15:42.640 --> 15:43.846
[FRED CLEARS THROAT]

15:44.000 --> 15:46.401
- Oh, those kinds of stakes.
- Aw.

15:48.200 --> 15:51.170
Look at these vampire jewels. Gorgeous.

15:51.320 --> 15:54.290
VAN HELSING: Those belonged
to an actual Vampire's bride...

15:54.440 --> 15:55.726
...in ancient Walachia.

15:56.040 --> 15:59.249
Looks like she scored
a wealthy vampire husband.

15:59.400 --> 16:00.925
VAN HELSING:
They're quite priceless.

16:01.080 --> 16:05.483
But those stones don't compare
to the real jewel of my collection.

16:05.880 --> 16:08.804
A face to launch 100 million fears.

16:08.960 --> 16:13.284
I bring you the dreaded vampire
Lord Valdronya.

16:13.800 --> 16:17.646
Entombed in glass
for nigh a thousand years.

16:17.960 --> 16:20.008
- Oh, my gosh.
- Wow!

16:20.160 --> 16:21.286
Awesome.

16:24.880 --> 16:28.168
- Looks fake to me.
- Me too.

16:34.600 --> 16:35.886
[BOTH SCREAM]

16:36.040 --> 16:37.929
The vampire lives!

16:38.080 --> 16:39.730
Guys, don't be ridiculous.

16:39.880 --> 16:42.326
- His eyes were glowing!
SCOOBY: Mm-hm.

16:42.480 --> 16:45.484
You'll have to excuse them.
They tend to be slightly excitable.

16:45.920 --> 16:47.888
Perfectly understandable.

16:48.040 --> 16:51.965
Lord Valdronya was quite
the fearsome fellow in his day.

16:52.120 --> 16:54.407
We're lucky he's sealed under glass now.

16:55.840 --> 16:57.649
This glass is so murky.

16:57.800 --> 17:02.567
- Ah, Velma, always the skeptic.
- Eh, it's my thing.

17:02.920 --> 17:05.605
Even if the vampire were alive,
he wouldn't get anywhere.

17:05.760 --> 17:07.683
This glass is 6 inches thick.

17:07.839 --> 17:10.650
If only Valdronya would wake...

17:10.800 --> 17:14.771
...I'd have tourists filling this place
like back in the day.

17:14.920 --> 17:16.922
And I wouldn't have
to rent my property...

17:17.079 --> 17:21.290
...to Lita Rutland's
traveling vampire festival just to get by.

17:21.440 --> 17:22.566
Sounds rough.

17:22.720 --> 17:26.611
Lita's threatened to pull out next year
if things don't pick up.

17:27.000 --> 17:30.891
I'm afraid I may not be able
to save my family's legacy.

17:31.280 --> 17:33.806
Then again,
you never know what will happen.

17:33.960 --> 17:37.123
Maybe my latest book
will become a best seller.

17:37.400 --> 17:39.687
You write books? That's fu... Ow.

17:39.840 --> 17:43.561
- Don't we have a show to see?
- Ah, yes. We'd better get going.

17:43.720 --> 17:46.644
The vampires await.

17:49.920 --> 17:50.921
[BOTH YELL]

17:51.080 --> 17:53.003
Wait for us!

17:58.040 --> 18:00.646
VAN HELSING: Our tickets are
being held in the box office. Wait here.

18:00.800 --> 18:02.484
I'll be right back.

18:02.640 --> 18:04.210
VELMA:
"Fangenschanz."

18:04.680 --> 18:06.045
Fangenschanz?

18:06.200 --> 18:07.247
I've heard of them.

18:07.400 --> 18:11.041
They're supposed to be the most amazing
vampire-themed theater troupe ever.

18:11.200 --> 18:13.851
Here, Scoob.
Wear this garlic for protection.

18:14.000 --> 18:17.243
- Vampires hate it.
- Yeah.

18:20.720 --> 18:23.246
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
you can't bring garlic in here.

18:23.400 --> 18:26.483
SHAGGY: "No wooden stakes, garlic
or flash photography."

18:26.680 --> 18:31.527
Huh. Well, I hate to let
perfectly good food go to waste.

18:37.360 --> 18:38.930
No garlic on us.

18:39.080 --> 18:43.130
Ugh. Gross. Just go inside.

18:44.760 --> 18:45.761
Weirdos.

18:51.360 --> 18:52.566
Hello.

18:52.720 --> 18:54.768
[WOMAN GRUNTING]

18:56.000 --> 18:59.209
Ew, someone's wearing
some stanky perfume.

18:59.360 --> 19:00.646
[SCOOBY & SHAGGY SNIFFING]

19:00.800 --> 19:04.566
- I don't smell it. Do you, Scoob?
- Nope.

19:04.720 --> 19:05.960
VELMA:
According to the program...

19:06.120 --> 19:10.125
...the members of Fangenschanz are so
dedicated to the vampire lifestyle...

19:10.280 --> 19:11.725
...they perform only at night.

19:12.080 --> 19:14.048
Method actors.

19:16.160 --> 19:18.083
[DRAMATIC ORCHESTRAL MUSIC
PLAYS OVER SPEAKERS]

19:20.040 --> 19:24.170
Ladies and gentle mortals,
it's feeding time.

19:24.320 --> 19:25.321
[UPBEAT JAZZ MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

19:25.480 --> 19:27.721
[SINGING]
<i>♪ What's that you hear?</i>

19:28.160 --> 19:30.766
<i>♪ The sound of fear</i>

19:31.240 --> 19:34.130
<i>♪ Because they're here</i>

19:34.760 --> 19:36.842
<i>♪ Vampires roaming the night</i>

19:37.360 --> 19:38.771
<i>♪ What's that you say?</i>

19:38.920 --> 19:40.126
[SNARLING]

19:40.280 --> 19:42.169
<i>♪ Can't be, no way</i>

19:42.320 --> 19:43.321
[GIRL SHRIEKS]

19:43.480 --> 19:46.768
<i>♪ They're fake?
♪ Okay</i>

19:46.920 --> 19:49.400
<i>♪ Believe whatever you might</i>

19:49.560 --> 19:52.803
<i>♪ But when the moon is full
♪ On a starlit night</i>

19:52.960 --> 19:56.009
<i>♪ You best all lock
your doors up light</i>

19:56.160 --> 20:01.121
<i>♪ Because, my friend
♪ The vampires start to dance</i>

20:01.880 --> 20:04.645
ACTORS:
<i>♪ And they're all around you</i>

20:05.480 --> 20:07.960
<i>♪ Everybody's coming to play</i>

20:08.120 --> 20:10.726
<i>♪ Oh, yes, they found you</i>

20:11.480 --> 20:13.960
<i>♪ And now they're
gonna lake you away</i>

20:14.120 --> 20:17.090
<i>♪ So watch out, lake care</i>

