<i>♪ Be smart, beware</i>

20:20.360 --> 20:23.091
<i>♪ Because out there</i>

20:23.760 --> 20:26.570
<i>♪ Something's waiting for you</i>

20:26.720 --> 20:29.963
<i>♪ When midnight comes,
it's time to hide</i>

20:30.120 --> 20:32.964
<i>♪ Say good night and run inside</i>

20:33.120 --> 20:38.524
<i>♪ Because that, my friend, is when
♪ They all come out again</i>

20:38.680 --> 20:43.561
<i>♪ Oh, yes, right now is when
♪ The vampires dance</i>

20:47.560 --> 20:48.800
<i>♪ The vampires dance. ♪</i>

20:49.200 --> 20:50.770
Boo!

20:52.000 --> 20:53.001
Yeah!

20:54.280 --> 20:55.725
[WHISTLES]

20:57.320 --> 20:59.926
What? I'm just showing my appreciation.

21:00.080 --> 21:03.209
[WHISTLING AND CHEERING]

21:04.800 --> 21:07.531
We welcome you,
friends and potential blood donors.

21:07.680 --> 21:10.286
And while we are mere performers,
be warned.

21:10.560 --> 21:15.646
If you fear the sight of a real living
vampire, please, leave now.

21:16.120 --> 21:17.281
That's our cue.

21:17.440 --> 21:19.204
[BOTH WHIMPERING]

21:23.320 --> 21:24.321
[BRAM LAUGHS]

21:24.480 --> 21:25.481
Too late.

21:25.640 --> 21:30.771
And now for the first time on any stage,
we shall attempt the unheard of:

21:30.920 --> 21:33.890
The Vampire's return from the grave.

21:34.040 --> 21:35.371
[LAUGHS]

21:36.440 --> 21:38.647
Wow, he's very good.

21:38.800 --> 21:41.201
Don't you guys think he's good?
Like, good?

21:41.360 --> 21:42.361
FRED:
Meh.

21:42.520 --> 21:47.162
Behold the ancient talisman
of the immortal blood-drinkers.

21:47.320 --> 21:51.564
Take heed, for the mortal world
shall soon be invaded.

21:51.720 --> 21:54.246
[ALL CHANTING IN ANCIENT TONGUE]

21:54.400 --> 21:58.883
<i>Blackest rose, wolf and bane
Bats and crows.</i>

21:59.040 --> 22:02.249
That spell is from
the ancient book of vampire.

22:02.400 --> 22:05.165
These jokers are playing
with supernatural fire.

22:05.320 --> 22:08.529
[CHANTING CONTINUES]

22:19.360 --> 22:20.361
[GASPS]

22:28.520 --> 22:30.249
What the...?

22:36.200 --> 22:37.326
[GUARD YELLS]

22:42.240 --> 22:44.129
[ACTORS SHOUT INDISTINCTLY]

22:44.280 --> 22:45.645
It's working?

22:47.320 --> 22:48.367
[ALL snum]

22:48.600 --> 22:49.601
Uh... Uh...

22:51.040 --> 22:52.041
[GRUNTS]

22:52.200 --> 22:55.329
This is bad. This is very bad.

22:56.240 --> 22:57.844
[GRUNTING]

23:02.280 --> 23:04.203
That's not Henry.

23:07.040 --> 23:08.041
Oh, no.

23:21.160 --> 23:23.128
[ROARS THEN SCREECHES]

23:26.080 --> 23:28.003
[LAUGHS]

23:29.000 --> 23:30.764
WOMAN:
Whoa.

23:30.920 --> 23:32.604
[WOMAN CHUCKLES]

23:32.760 --> 23:34.125
[CHATTERING]

23:37.320 --> 23:38.321
[SCOOBY WHIMPERING]

23:38.480 --> 23:41.802
- Next year, we're going to Miami.
- Yeah.

23:41.960 --> 23:46.602
I was getting ready before the show
when I was attacked by that vampire.

23:46.760 --> 23:47.886
Are you sure?

23:48.640 --> 23:52.326
Unless you know someone else with
massive fangs and glowing green eyes.

23:52.480 --> 23:56.610
I guess he put me under some sort of spell
and I passed out.

23:57.320 --> 24:00.961
That resurrection chant
was from the ancient book of vampire.

24:01.120 --> 24:03.202
Where on earth did you learn it?

24:03.560 --> 24:05.369
Um, the Internet.

24:05.920 --> 24:10.687
Well, I am afraid you may have unleashed
an unholy terror upon us all.

24:10.840 --> 24:13.571
Maybe we shouldn't
jump to conclusions just yet.

24:13.720 --> 24:15.848
Yeah, I'm sure this nice young man...

24:16.000 --> 24:18.765
Uh, I didn't get your name. Oh.

24:19.840 --> 24:22.286
Bram. And you are?

24:22.680 --> 24:23.761
[CHUCKLES]

24:23.920 --> 24:26.002
Bram. I mean, Daphne.

24:26.160 --> 24:28.401
I'm not Bram, you are. Ha-ha-ha.

24:28.560 --> 24:30.528
Oh. What were we talking about?

24:30.680 --> 24:34.571
We were saying we don't know for sure
that Valdronya escaped from his tomb.

24:36.320 --> 24:38.846
Oh. Uh, we should check that out.

24:39.000 --> 24:40.161
You kids go ahead.

24:40.520 --> 24:45.003
I'll stick around here to have a word
with the actors.

24:48.560 --> 24:50.130
You guys can't hide forever.

24:50.280 --> 24:53.921
SHAGGY: Care to try us?
- No. Let's go.

24:58.800 --> 25:00.211
SHAGGY: Careful.
GUARD: Unh.

25:00.360 --> 25:04.445
- He's been bitten.
- Hmm. Maybe. Or...

25:04.600 --> 25:06.090
VELMA:
We've got bigger problems.

25:06.760 --> 25:09.764
Unh. This lid is still sealed tight.

25:09.920 --> 25:12.651
Well, that vampire couldn't have
just walked through the glass.

25:12.800 --> 25:13.801
[GLASS SHATTERS]

25:13.960 --> 25:15.200
[MAN LAUGHING]

25:15.360 --> 25:17.488
The vampire queen's jewels are gone.

25:17.640 --> 25:18.971
Jinkies.

25:19.320 --> 25:20.845
[BOTH GASP]

25:21.000 --> 25:23.367
[VAMPIRE LAUGHS THEN SCREECHES]

25:23.520 --> 25:24.760
DAPHNE:
Duck!

25:24.920 --> 25:26.604
No, bat!

25:30.120 --> 25:32.521
Such beauty and innocence...

25:33.000 --> 25:35.731
...with the countenance of a queen.

25:36.280 --> 25:38.328
My queen.

25:38.480 --> 25:40.847
Your queen?

25:41.000 --> 25:42.286
FRED:
I don't think so.

25:42.440 --> 25:44.249
[VALDRONYA GRUNTS]

25:45.760 --> 25:47.364
[SHAGGY GRUNTS]

25:48.960 --> 25:49.961
[SNARLS]

25:53.760 --> 25:59.130
Yeah, there's no such thing
as real vampires, until now.

26:00.840 --> 26:04.845
There's a beast on the loose,
a spawn of the netherworld.

26:05.000 --> 26:10.086
I say it's time we shut this foul fair down
for the good of the community.

26:15.400 --> 26:17.926
Uh, set it up over there
by that rabble rouser.

26:19.040 --> 26:21.771
Hello, Kelly Smith
from <i>KDTV Action 10 News.</i>

26:22.120 --> 26:25.761
Looks like someone spilled the beans
about our escaped vampire.

26:25.920 --> 26:28.127
The audience thought
it was all part of the show.

26:28.280 --> 26:30.886
- Hope you're not implying my performers-
- I leaked it.

26:31.040 --> 26:32.087
You? But..

26:32.240 --> 26:34.766
This could be just the thing we need
to boost attendance.

26:34.920 --> 26:38.242
Ah. They do say there's no such thing
as bad publicity.

26:38.400 --> 26:42.450
That's the spirit. Now,
which would you say is my good side?

26:42.880 --> 26:46.771
VAN HELSING: I am so relieved
that none of you kids were hurt last night.

26:46.920 --> 26:50.003
Not physically,
but the mental wounds run deep.

26:50.160 --> 26:52.447
Yeah, run deep.

26:52.600 --> 26:57.162
Those foolish actors have no idea
the monster they've set loose.

26:57.480 --> 26:59.562
We can't be certain this is their doing.

26:59.720 --> 27:02.200
Or that we've got a real vampire
on our hands.

27:02.360 --> 27:04.362
Did you check the museum's
security system?

27:04.520 --> 27:06.488
Yep, the cameras recorded nothing.

27:06.640 --> 27:11.043
System's on the fritz, but I just
can't afford to fix it right now.

27:11.200 --> 27:13.009
Let's say it is a real vampire.

27:13.160 --> 27:15.561
How did he escape that sealed tomb?

27:16.840 --> 27:20.083
A living vampire can transform into mist.

27:20.240 --> 27:23.403
All it would need
is a tiny gap in the glass.

27:23.560 --> 27:26.928
This could all be a diversion
to steal those jewels. Just saying.

27:27.080 --> 27:28.969
GUARD:
Oh, what a night.

27:29.120 --> 27:30.963
Thanks for letting me sleep here, boss.

27:31.120 --> 27:34.329
No problem, Daniel.
I hope you're feeling better.

27:34.480 --> 27:36.528
Neck's a little sore,
but other than that...

27:37.000 --> 27:38.764
[BOTH SCREAM]

27:40.040 --> 27:41.371
The bite of the beast.

27:41.520 --> 27:43.409
He could turn batty any second.

27:43.560 --> 27:48.691
Doubtful. If he had been bitten
by a vampire, could he survive this?

27:49.120 --> 27:51.407
Sunlight makes a vampire explode.

27:51.920 --> 27:54.287
Wow, gorgeous day outside.

27:54.440 --> 27:57.171
- Huh?
- He didn't crumble to dust.

27:57.640 --> 28:02.328
He could be one of the rare few with
an antibody resistant to vampire venom.

28:02.480 --> 28:04.005
Or he wasn't bitten at all.

28:04.160 --> 28:06.766
Those look more like blisters than bites.

28:07.880 --> 28:10.406
When you were attacked, did it feel like...

28:10.560 --> 28:13.291
...oh, I don't know,
a thousand volts of electricity?

28:13.440 --> 28:16.489
Uh, actually, yeah. How'd you know?

28:16.640 --> 28:18.847
I volunteer at the police academy
on weekends.

28:19.000 --> 28:21.651
If there's one thing I know,
it's Taser burns.

28:22.520 --> 28:23.885
[GRUNTING AND YELLING]

28:24.040 --> 28:25.644
That tickles.

28:26.960 --> 28:30.362
- Pretty good detective work, pal.
- Thanks.

28:30.520 --> 28:33.330
Well, we also found your Taser
lying on the ground next to you.

28:34.760 --> 28:37.081
I must've tripped and zapped myself.
Huh.

28:37.240 --> 28:39.891
Weird.
I'd better go put that in my report.

28:40.040 --> 28:43.840
That explains the bite marks,
but how do you explain the vampire?

28:44.000 --> 28:47.368
So many questions.
It's quite the conundrum.

28:47.520 --> 28:49.090
A real whodunit.

28:49.240 --> 28:51.242
We'll need to put our heads together
on this one.

28:51.400 --> 28:52.811
Uh-oh.

28:52.960 --> 28:54.883
I know where this is going.

28:55.040 --> 28:59.841
Yep, I'd say we've got a real live
boney fide mystery on our hands.

29:00.160 --> 29:01.400
Eyewitness accounts aside...

29:01.560 --> 29:04.530
...we've had no confirmation
of the supposed vampires' existence...

29:04.680 --> 29:06.523
...from anyone associated with the fair.

29:06.680 --> 29:08.364
LITA:
You want confirmation?

29:09.120 --> 29:10.360
No one is safe.

29:10.520 --> 29:12.807
I'm here to tell you
from firsthand experience...

29:12.960 --> 29:14.610
...that vampires bite.

29:14.760 --> 29:17.161
So much for keeping this
on the down-low.

