You guys see what you can dig up.

32:47.680 --> 32:49.125
POUBELLE:
...Overreacting.

32:49.280 --> 32:54.764
But ignore this warning
and you'll be knocking on the doors to...

32:54.920 --> 32:59.209
Shaggy, you and Scooby stand watch.
If anyone comes, tap on the door.

33:00.200 --> 33:01.201
We're in.

33:03.400 --> 33:04.925
[SQUEAK]

33:05.080 --> 33:06.684
Wow, what a wreck.

33:06.840 --> 33:11.323
They may be moral and wholesome,
but they're not very clean.

33:11.480 --> 33:14.529
We've got hundreds of reports
of vampire sightings.

33:14.680 --> 33:18.287
Couldn't people be imagining these things
because you're causing them to panic?

33:18.440 --> 33:20.522
I didn't create the evil.

33:20.680 --> 33:24.651
Maybe not, but you sure seem to be eager
to take advantage of it.

33:24.800 --> 33:27.485
Young lady, your questions
were not cleared with my staff.

33:27.640 --> 33:29.244
Someone check her credentials.

33:29.400 --> 33:31.482
Uh, I think I left them in the car.

33:32.600 --> 33:34.170
Fred, I found something.

33:34.320 --> 33:37.164
Ew, I hope it's not more spiders.

33:45.680 --> 33:47.842
"Poubelle for mayor"?

33:52.360 --> 33:54.124
What are you two doing back here?

33:54.920 --> 33:56.251
SHAGGY: Um, uh...
SCOOBY: Uh... Uh...

33:56.400 --> 33:58.448
- We're, uh...
- We're door inspectors.

33:58.600 --> 34:00.887
Stand back. This one might explode.

34:01.040 --> 34:02.041
[SHAGGY & SCOOBY GRUNT]

34:02.200 --> 34:03.725
Doors don't explo...

34:05.400 --> 34:06.447
Why'd you signal?

34:07.120 --> 34:08.690
Stay right where you are.

34:08.840 --> 34:10.967
Run away!

34:12.679 --> 34:14.011
[SHAGGY YELLS]

34:16.199 --> 34:17.326
[TIRES SCREECHING]

34:17.639 --> 34:19.005
Get in!

34:19.560 --> 34:21.801
GUARD:
Hey, stop that thing! Stop!

34:23.199 --> 34:25.009
[ALL SIGH]

34:29.840 --> 34:31.569
DAPHNE:
Poubelle is running for office.

34:31.719 --> 34:33.051
That explains a lot.

34:33.199 --> 34:35.806
He's using the vampire to get attention
for his movement...

34:35.960 --> 34:37.688
...and boost his upcoming campaign.

34:37.840 --> 34:40.844
Still, it isn't proof
he's behind the vampire attacks.

34:41.000 --> 34:43.446
He's just using them to his advantage.

34:43.600 --> 34:45.489
This fog is like soup.

34:47.360 --> 34:49.089
Maybe you should let me drive.

34:49.239 --> 34:51.242
I'm good. Sort of enjoying it.

34:51.400 --> 34:53.004
[SNARLS]
[ALL SCREAMING]

35:06.600 --> 35:08.011
[VALDRONYA GRUNTING]

35:10.440 --> 35:12.363
[DAPHNE SHRIEKING]

35:13.280 --> 35:14.281
[THUD]

35:14.440 --> 35:16.647
[VALDRONYA LAUGHS THEN SNARLS]

35:16.800 --> 35:18.404
Daphne, look out!

35:19.840 --> 35:21.490
Brace yourselves!

35:22.600 --> 35:23.726
[ALL SCREAMING]

35:29.480 --> 35:32.051
That opening is too tight.
We won't make it.

35:32.560 --> 35:33.925
[DAPHNE GASPS]

35:34.080 --> 35:35.730
[SHRIEKS]

35:43.400 --> 35:45.687
I'm telling you, Poubelle,
you can't come in here.

35:45.840 --> 35:47.365
You're scaring off my customers.

35:47.520 --> 35:52.651
And I'm telling you, I've got a special
dispensation from the sheriff himself.

35:52.800 --> 35:53.961
That's right, Ms. Rutland.

35:54.120 --> 35:56.851
By order of the court,
I have recruited these gentlemen.

35:57.000 --> 36:00.971
We are hereby deputized
vampire hunters.

36:01.320 --> 36:02.401
[SIGHS]

36:04.040 --> 36:07.089
Vampire hunters, ho!

36:07.240 --> 36:08.480
MAN: All right.
WOMAN: Let's go.

36:08.640 --> 36:10.210
[CHATTERING]

36:13.120 --> 36:15.964
Who would actually fall
for that scaremonger's rantings?

36:16.120 --> 36:18.600
They say there's a fraidycat
born every minute.

36:18.760 --> 36:22.526
Ah, there you are. I got us all
neck protectors, just to be safe.

36:22.680 --> 36:24.011
I see your point, Velma.

36:24.160 --> 36:25.764
Hey, where are Scooby and Shaggy?

36:25.920 --> 36:28.366
They went to the food court
to calm their nerves.

36:28.520 --> 36:30.170
Heh. Those guys are so jumpy.

36:30.320 --> 36:31.321
[NOISEMAKER RATTLING]

36:31.480 --> 36:33.608
FRED:
Yaah! A vampire!

36:34.040 --> 36:36.850
The food court should be right here
behind the theater.

36:39.960 --> 36:42.930
Unless the map is upside down.

36:43.080 --> 36:44.809
[SCOOBY CHUCKLES]

36:47.560 --> 36:51.565
Careful. Damage anything
and we're as good as dead.

36:51.720 --> 36:54.769
What are you doing back here?
This is a restricted area.

36:54.920 --> 36:58.288
We're just looking for the food court.

36:58.440 --> 36:59.566
Uh-oh.

36:59.720 --> 37:02.041
- We can't let them go.
- What if they tell someone...

37:02.200 --> 37:04.282
- ...what they've seen?
- You're right.

37:04.440 --> 37:06.169
Uh, what have we seen?

37:06.320 --> 37:08.209
Scooby, I think we're in...

37:08.360 --> 37:12.365
Hey, look, a Hollywood talent scout.

37:13.160 --> 37:14.605
[BOTH WHIMPERING]

37:16.440 --> 37:17.805
I think we lost them.

37:17.960 --> 37:19.086
[GROWLING]

37:19.240 --> 37:20.480
BOTH:
Huh?

37:20.640 --> 37:24.361
We better find that food court, Scoob
Your tummy's grumbling.

37:24.520 --> 37:26.443
Not mine.

37:26.600 --> 37:28.284
Well, it isn't mine.

37:28.440 --> 37:29.965
[SNARLING]

37:30.640 --> 37:32.130
[ROARS]

37:32.280 --> 37:34.681
Stay back or I'll be forced to use this.

37:35.240 --> 37:36.241
[ROARS]

37:36.400 --> 37:38.402
Maybe later!

37:41.800 --> 37:43.006
[SHAGGY YELLING]

37:44.200 --> 37:46.441
I've been bitten by a vampire!

37:46.600 --> 37:47.726
[GIRL GASPS]

37:47.880 --> 37:50.451
Look, Mama, a real vampire.

37:51.360 --> 37:52.361
[SNARLING]

38:12.040 --> 38:13.485
[ROARS]

38:17.000 --> 38:18.923
[HUMMING]

38:19.320 --> 38:21.004
SHAGGY:
Incoming!

38:21.160 --> 38:22.605
[YELLING]

38:27.240 --> 38:31.086
Phew. He's gone, Scoob.
And I'm a goner.

38:31.240 --> 38:33.402
I've been bitten by a vampire.

38:33.560 --> 38:37.087
I'll probably sprout fangs any second
and...

38:37.240 --> 38:39.049
Is this ketchup?

38:42.240 --> 38:43.924
Bloodsuckers!

38:44.080 --> 38:45.127
BOTH:
Where?

38:45.280 --> 38:47.248
That one shape-shifted into a dog.

38:47.400 --> 38:48.401
Uh-oh.

38:48.560 --> 38:50.767
- I think they mean us.
- Get them!

38:50.920 --> 38:53.082
[CROWD SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

38:57.440 --> 39:00.569
Appears we lost
them crafty shape-shifters.

39:00.720 --> 39:03.883
I guess we best head back
before our torches burn out.

39:04.040 --> 39:05.485
MAN 1: Yeah.
WOMAN: All right.

39:05.640 --> 39:07.802
MAN 2:
Oh, well. Maybe next time.

39:09.440 --> 39:13.809
Ah. Phew. We're safe, Scoob.
Except for the fact we're lost in a swamp.

39:13.960 --> 39:17.009
And I could turn into a vampire
at any moment.

39:24.280 --> 39:25.805
[GRUNTS THEN WHIMPERING]

39:30.640 --> 39:33.803
Check out my bite. Is it bad?

39:38.720 --> 39:41.166
Don't sugarcoat it. I know I'm done for.

39:41.520 --> 39:44.842
You should get out of here
before I turn all bat-ified.

39:45.360 --> 39:47.840
Uh-uh. I'm not going.

39:49.080 --> 39:51.321
Once the vampire venom
takes hold of my system...

39:51.480 --> 39:54.962
...there's no guarantee
I won't sink my fangs into you.

39:55.120 --> 39:56.770
We have to split up, Scoob.

39:57.160 --> 39:58.446
No, Shaggy. No.

39:59.240 --> 40:01.083
It's the only way to save yourself.

40:01.240 --> 40:04.801
Just turn away from me
and don't look back.

40:04.960 --> 40:07.281
[SCOOBY WHIMPERING]

40:08.360 --> 40:10.010
I can't.

40:15.080 --> 40:18.289
I guess I'll have to do this myself.

40:18.680 --> 40:20.250
Huh?

40:21.640 --> 40:23.244
SHAGGY:
Goodbye, old friend.

40:23.640 --> 40:26.769
I hope one day you'll see that
this is best for both of us.

40:27.400 --> 40:28.845
Shaggy?

40:30.440 --> 40:32.363
[WHIMPERING]

40:35.560 --> 40:37.881
One foot in front of the other.

40:38.040 --> 40:40.850
Don't look back. Don't ever look--

40:44.480 --> 40:46.403
[WHIMPERING]

40:55.400 --> 40:56.811
I looked back.

40:56.960 --> 40:58.450
[LAUGHS]

41:09.160 --> 41:10.207
[SCOOBY LAUGHS]

41:10.600 --> 41:13.809
- Shaggy.
- Promise you'll never leave me, Scoob.

41:13.960 --> 41:15.530
Never.

41:15.840 --> 41:17.729
[CHUCKLES]

41:21.120 --> 41:22.849
Wha--? What are you doing?

41:23.000 --> 41:26.083
Checking for vampire symptoms.
Say "ah."

41:26.240 --> 41:27.241
Ah.

41:27.400 --> 41:31.246
Scoob, you're the best pal
a guy could have.

41:31.400 --> 41:34.006
A real friend to the end.

41:34.160 --> 41:36.731
[SINGING] <i>♪ Whenever I'm down
♪ Right there on the ground</i>

41:36.880 --> 41:39.451
<i>♪ Lying out flat on my face</i>

41:39.600 --> 41:41.967
<i>♪Who is the pup
♪ Picking me up</i>

41:42.120 --> 41:44.521
<i>♪ And gelling me back in the race?</i>

41:45.040 --> 41:50.001
<i>♪ Who'll be around and watching my back
♪ Guide me along and keep me on track?</i>

41:50.160 --> 41:52.208
<i>♪ Forever he's there
♪ We're a pair</i>

41:52.360 --> 41:55.011
<i>♪ Scooby and me</i>

41:55.480 --> 41:56.686
<i>♪ When the going gels tough</i>

41:56.840 --> 41:58.285
<i>♪ - And things can gel
♪ - Rough</i>

41:58.440 --> 42:00.761
<i>♪ - You're the one on whom I depend
♪ - Who, me?</i>

42:00.920 --> 42:03.400
<i>♪ - I'll give you the proof, I'll' climb up on the--
♪ - Roof</i>

42:03.560 --> 42:05.130
<i>♪ And shout to the world
♪ "You're my friend!"</i>

42:05.280 --> 42:06.281
[HOWLS]

42:06.440 --> 42:08.841
<i>♪ And when I'm a vampire
♪ Roaming the night</i>

42:09.000 --> 42:11.480
<i>♪ Because you're my pal
♪ I'll just lake a small bile</i>

42:11.640 --> 42:13.563
<i>♪ You're one of the greats
♪ And we're males</i>

42:13.720 --> 42:14.926
<i>♪ Scooby and me</i>

42:15.080 --> 42:16.081
[SCOOBY CHUCKLES]

42:16.240 --> 42:17.571
<i>♪ Oh, Scooby and me</i>

42:17.720 --> 42:21.770
<i>♪ We're gonna be together for good
♪ That buddy of mine</i>

42:21.920 --> 42:24.287
<i>♪ If you're ever in doubt
♪ Need me helping you out</i>

42:24.440 --> 42:26.920
<i>♪ You know that would if I got time</i>

42:27.080 --> 42:29.731
<i>♪ If you're ever in jail
♪ And you're needing some bail</i>

42:30.240 --> 42:31.685
<i>♪ Or a friend to set you free</i>

42:31.840 --> 42:32.841
[SCOOBY YELLS]

42:33.000 --> 42:35.401
<i>♪ You can always count on me</i>

42:35.760 --> 42:38.127
<i>♪ 'Cause tell me where would I be</i>

42:38.360 --> 42:41.330
<i>♪ Without you by my side
♪ My friend and my guide</i>

42:41.480 --> 42:44.006
<i>♪ Helping to carry me through</i>

42:44.160 --> 42:46.606
<i>♪ People go by
♪ If I live or I die</i>

42:46.760 --> 42:49.001
<i>♪ They wouldn't care, but not you</i>

42:49.560 --> 42:51.881
<i>♪ You are the one who keeps me at ease</i>

42:52.240 --> 42:54.607
<i>♪ - Giving me love and occasional fleas
♪ - Sorry</i>

42:54.760 --> 42:56.728
<i>♪ No matter what comes
♪ We are chums</i>

42:56.880 --> 42:58.006
<i>♪ Scooby and me ♪</i>

42:58.160 --> 42:59.161
Yep.

42:59.320 --> 43:00.526
[LAUGHS]

43:02.520 --> 43:08.209
In the interest of public safety, I am
hereby issuing a dusk-to-dawn curfew.

43:08.360 --> 43:10.761
- No one is to be out past dark.
POUBELLE: Yes!

43:10.920 --> 43:12.684
[CROWD CHEERING]

43:12.840 --> 43:15.161
Now that is more like it.

43:15.720 --> 43:19.884
This extreme measure is seen as a victory
for local anti-vampire crusader...

43:20.040 --> 43:22.611
...and now mayoral candidate,
Jesper Poubelle.

43:23.240 --> 43:25.607
[SINGING] <i>♪Closing us down
♪But that isn't fair</i>

43:25.760 --> 43:28.240
<i>♪ I'm warning you all
♪ You belle! Beware</i>

43:28.400 --> 43:30.209
<i>♪ You're messing with me
♪ And you'll see</i>

43:30.360 --> 43:32.840
<i>♪ You're all gonna pay</i>

43:34.000 --> 43:38.767
<i>♪ Oh, I'm broke, I'm ruined
♪ What will I do?</i>

43:39.360 --> 43:44.321
<i>♪ Oh, what happens
♪ When the rent is due?</i>

43:44.720 --> 43:49.601
<i>♪Oh, watch out, my friends
♪ There's vampires on the loose</i>

43:49.760 --> 43:52.206
<i>♪ And that's why I brought the noose</i>

43:52.360 --> 43:54.886
<i>♪ You just kif fed
the golden goose ♪</i>

43:55.400 --> 43:57.926
ACTORS: <i> Oh, got a show to do</i>
CROWD: <i>Vampires here.</i>

43:58.080 --> 43:59.605
ACTORS: <i>Curtain up</i>
CROWD: <i>Run them out of town.</i>

43:59.760 --> 44:00.761
<i>Hey, Scooby-Doo.</i>

44:00.920 --> 44:03.002
ACTORS: <i>Opening night revue</i>
CROWD: <i>Bad show.</i>

44:03.160 --> 44:05.162
ACTORS: <i>Don't give up</i>
CROWD: <i>It's time to shut them down.</i>

44:05.320 --> 44:06.526
<i>What would! do?</i>

44:06.680 --> 44:09.001
<i>They're to blame, it's true.</i>

44:09.160 --> 44:11.731
<i>Poubelle, shame on you.</i>

44:11.880 --> 44:14.042
<i>We're not the same as you.</i>

44:14.200 --> 44:15.770
<i>Where would I be without you?</i>

44:15.920 --> 44:16.967
[HOWLS]

44:17.120 --> 44:19.361
<i>Scooby and me We always will be.</i>

44:19.520 --> 44:22.330
<i>- Together forever as friends.
- Gel out, don't want vampires.</i>

44:22.480 --> 44:24.881
<i>- You are the one, second to none.
- Leave us because.</i>

44:25.040 --> 44:27.691
<i>- The pal on which a buddy depends.
- We know the show goes on.</i>

44:27.840 --> 44:30.286
<i>They are the ones
They're evil and bad.</i>

44:30.440 --> 44:33.125
<i>Watch out for them
They're crazy and mad.</i>

44:33.280 --> 44:36.363
<i>What do you do when there's vampires
Where there shouldn't be?</i>

44:36.520 --> 44:38.841
<i>- Listen to me.
- You can't do this to me.</i>

44:39.000 --> 44:40.206
<i>Doesn't anyone see?</i>

44:40.360 --> 44:41.441
<i>Why'd this happen to me?</i>

44:41.600 --> 44:45.446
<i>It's always going to be
Scooby and me</i>

44:47.880 --> 44:49.928
[BIRD SQUAWKING]

44:51.400 --> 44:53.164
Scooby, I think we've got company.

44:53.320 --> 44:54.321
[ANIMAL TRILLING]

44:54.480 --> 44:55.481
[SNAKE HISSING]

44:55.640 --> 44:56.880
[SHAGGY & SCOOBY WHIMPERING]

44:58.440 --> 45:01.444
<i>But critics call the move shortsighted and
a slinging blow to the local economy.</i>

45:01.600 --> 45:02.681
[VAN HELSING SIGHS]

45:02.840 --> 45:06.322
<i>It's an assault on capitalism.
Disgusting.</i>

45:06.480 --> 45:09.290
<i>This is the last time I bring my fair
to this Podunk town.</i>

45:10.160 --> 45:15.451
Without the income from Lita's festival,
there's no way I can keep this place afloat.

45:15.600 --> 45:16.965
I'm ruined.

45:17.120 --> 45:20.329
We'll try to solve this mystery
before Lita packs up for good.

45:20.480 --> 45:22.130
Thank you, Velma.

45:22.280 --> 45:24.282
I'm really lucky to have you kids here.

45:24.440 --> 45:25.805
FRED:
Hey, guys.

45:25.960 --> 45:27.724
I'm worried about Shaggy and Scooby.

45:27.880 --> 45:29.609
I haven't seen them since last night.

45:29.760 --> 45:33.003
They probably got spooked by
their own shadows and hid out all night.

45:33.160 --> 45:35.083
I just hope the vampire didn't get them.

45:35.240 --> 45:37.811
I highly doubt we're dealing
with a real vampire.

45:37.960 --> 45:39.041
Show him, Daphne.

45:39.440 --> 45:42.887
I found this in the Mystery Machine.
It's a piece of the Vampire's cloak.

45:43.040 --> 45:44.963
I must've torn it loose
when he attacked us.

45:45.960 --> 45:48.008
What's an old piece of fabric
gonna prove?

45:48.160 --> 45:49.321
It's not old.

45:49.480 --> 45:54.407
It's clearly poly-krillion, a synthetic
material first produced in 1997.

45:54.560 --> 45:56.289
Girlfriend knows her fabrics.

45:56.440 --> 45:57.441
[CHUCKLES]

45:57.600 --> 46:02.128
So the vampire, or whatever it was,
probably isn't a thousand years old.

46:02.280 --> 46:03.441
Oh, what a relief.

46:03.600 --> 46:07.241
I mean, not that I thought
we were dealing with a real vampire.

46:07.400 --> 46:08.970
That would be dumb to think that.

46:09.880 --> 46:11.564
Actually I must confess...

46:11.720 --> 46:15.850
...the outfit Valdronya was wearing
in his tomb was new.

46:16.000 --> 46:19.561
How? You said he was sealed in his tomb
for a thousand years.

46:19.720 --> 46:22.769
Yes, but his clothing
had disintegrated overtime.

46:23.240 --> 46:28.690
We unsealed him briefly for authentication
and in the name of modesty.

46:28.840 --> 46:33.971
Valdronya's clothing had disintegrated,
but he didn't. That's odd.

46:34.120 --> 46:38.569
A vampire is a living being,
even in a state of slumber.

46:38.720 --> 46:41.644
This is what's left
of his original garments.

46:42.280 --> 46:43.691
Antique Asian silk.

46:43.840 --> 46:46.889
Spun gold markings.
The thick hand weave.

46:47.040 --> 46:49.930
Fabric like this hasn't been made
for 500 years.

46:50.080 --> 46:53.766
Valdronya is still out there.

46:54.280 --> 46:56.203
Think I'll just grab these things.

46:56.360 --> 46:57.930
[WHISTLES]

46:58.080 --> 47:03.086
I'm afraid those actors unleashed
an unholy terror upon us all.

47:03.240 --> 47:05.447
Yes, the actors.

47:05.600 --> 47:08.171
Ooh. I'll go check them out.

47:08.800 --> 47:10.131
I bet you will.

47:10.280 --> 47:12.886
Freddy, do I detect a little
twinge of jealousy?

47:13.040 --> 47:18.080
Me, jealous of some vitamin D-deprived,
historical vampire reenactment nuts?

47:18.240 --> 47:19.890
[CHUCKLES]

47:20.040 --> 47:21.280
Maybe I should go with you.

47:21.440 --> 47:24.444
No, thanks.
I'm well prepared to handle Bram.

47:24.600 --> 47:27.126
Uh... I mean, the actors. Bye.

47:27.280 --> 47:28.930
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

47:29.080 --> 47:30.081
Hmm.

47:33.720 --> 47:36.644
Hello? Anyone in here?

47:55.920 --> 47:57.331
[CLANGING]

48:00.520 --> 48:02.682
Strange place for a laser projector.

48:08.200 --> 48:09.201
[DAPHNE SHRIEKS]

48:09.360 --> 48:12.364
Bram. Don't sneak up on a girl like that.

48:12.520 --> 48:14.284
I wasn't the one sneaking.

48:14.440 --> 48:18.286
You looking for something or someone?

48:18.440 --> 48:21.330
Actually, I... Do you sleep up there?

48:21.480 --> 48:25.280
To know the vampire,
you must become the vampire.

48:25.640 --> 48:27.688
Hm. You're really committed.

48:27.840 --> 48:30.207
It's the role I was meant for.

48:30.360 --> 48:34.410
So do you lurk around
darkened theaters often?

48:34.720 --> 48:36.085
More than you know.

48:36.240 --> 48:38.971
Well, there's something
we have in common...

48:39.120 --> 48:42.090
- ...right off the bat.
- Cute.

48:42.760 --> 48:45.604
Grab on. I'll teach you to fly.

48:45.960 --> 48:48.645
I don't know. Promise not to drop me?

48:48.800 --> 48:51.565
Only a fool would drop a girl like you.

48:51.720 --> 48:53.324
Smooth.

48:57.160 --> 48:59.731
Wow, this is amazing.

48:59.880 --> 49:01.484
It's fate that brought you here.

49:02.120 --> 49:04.930
Destiny. A cosmic occurrence.

49:05.080 --> 49:07.128
A vision foretold.

49:07.280 --> 49:08.805
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

49:08.960 --> 49:13.841
Bram, I think you're very interesting,
but you're one cliché from my limit.

49:14.000 --> 49:15.331
Daphne.

49:17.240 --> 49:20.528
[SINGING]
<i>♪ From the moment you'd first seen us</i>

49:21.000 --> 49:24.402
<i>♪ Did you ever in your life think
♪ You'd be standing here with me?</i>

49:24.560 --> 49:27.643
<i>♪ With this thing we have between us</i>

49:27.960 --> 49:31.009
<i>♪ I could tell that it was fate
♪ And it was always meant to be</i>

49:31.160 --> 49:34.607
<i>♪ Yes, you and! were meant for glory</i>

49:34.920 --> 49:39.084
<i>♪ And something greater
♪ Than this drab little world that we see</i>

49:39.240 --> 49:41.811
<i>♪ And who'd have thought that later</i>

49:42.240 --> 49:44.049
<i>♪ You and! would have this dale</i>

49:44.200 --> 49:45.406
<i>♪ A dale with destiny</i>

49:45.560 --> 49:48.848
<i>♪ I can't believe you think I'd buy that</i>

49:49.160 --> 49:52.528
<i>♪ Come on, I've heard this all before
♪ It's just a line, I'm not naive</i>

49:52.680 --> 49:55.889
<i>♪ I really can't believe you'd try that</i>

49:56.160 --> 49:59.721
<i>♪ I've gotta say you must be nuts
♪ To think that's something I'd believe</i>

49:59.880 --> 50:02.645
<i>♪ You lay it on there kind of heavy</i>

50:03.240 --> 50:07.450
<i>♪ With all this talk of something special
♪ So, what could it be?</i>

50:07.600 --> 50:12.561
<i>♪ What if I say I know a way
♪ To immortality? ♪</i>

50:12.720 --> 50:13.721
Really?

50:13.880 --> 50:17.248
[SINGING]
<i>♪ You and! could live forever</i>

50:17.400 --> 50:19.482
<i>♪ You mean our lives would never end?</i>

50:19.640 --> 50:20.766
<i>♪ That's right</i>

50:21.120 --> 50:22.770
<i>♪ And we won't be aging ever?</i>

50:24.720 --> 50:26.609
<i>♪ You'd be Bram's immortal friend</i>

50:26.760 --> 50:28.205
<i>♪ - For real?
♪ - That's the deal</i>

50:28.360 --> 50:31.682
<i>♪ - Can't you feel, it's so exciting?
♪ - Everlasting life eternal</i>

50:31.840 --> 50:35.083
<i>♪ You've been chosen for this honor
♪ You'll have wealth and you'll have fame</i>

50:35.240 --> 50:37.083
<i>♪ I gotta write this in my journal</i>

50:37.240 --> 50:40.369
<i>♪ Just wail and see
♪ Everyone will know your name</i>

50:40.520 --> 50:42.363
<i>♪ - Will I slay cute?
♪ - Absolute</i>

50:42.520 --> 50:45.490
BOTH:
<i>♪ We'll be going down in history</i>

50:45.760 --> 50:49.003
<i>♪ We'll be known throughout the world</i>

50:49.480 --> 50:52.882
<i>♪ Eternity for you and me</i>

50:53.040 --> 50:55.805
<i>♪ Let's live forever and ever</i>

50:55.960 --> 50:57.803
<i>♪ Yes, never to sever</i>

50:57.960 --> 51:00.725
<i>♪ Together forever, we'll be</i>

51:00.880 --> 51:02.291
<i>♪ You and me ♪</i>

51:05.120 --> 51:07.327
I'm gonna have to say thanks, but no.

51:07.480 --> 51:08.686
Points for trying though.

51:08.840 --> 51:10.922
This makes us very unhappy.

51:11.080 --> 51:13.481
Well, I'm sorry, but... Us?

51:16.920 --> 51:17.921
[ALL SNARLING]

51:19.720 --> 51:21.961
Seize the Vampire's bride.

51:22.120 --> 51:23.406
The what?

51:35.960 --> 51:37.883
[GRUNTS]

51:38.560 --> 51:40.483
[YAWNS]

51:42.720 --> 51:43.846
Where are we?

51:44.000 --> 51:46.446
No clue, Scoob. Not that it matters.

51:46.600 --> 51:50.446
This swamp is as good a home as any
for a vampire and his canine pal.

51:51.360 --> 51:54.443
- Except for the leeches.
- Leeches?

51:54.600 --> 51:56.602
[BOTH YELLING]

51:58.880 --> 51:59.881
[BOTH SIGH]

52:00.040 --> 52:04.523
But, hey, we won't let a few little leeches
spoil things, will we, Scoob?

52:04.680 --> 52:05.966
No way.

52:06.120 --> 52:08.202
[CHUCKLES]

52:08.520 --> 52:10.284
[BOTH YELL]

52:10.440 --> 52:11.885
SHAGGY:
Snake!

52:13.640 --> 52:14.846
Gators!

52:18.360 --> 52:20.283
Crawdads!

52:20.440 --> 52:23.011
Snakes and gators and crawdads.
Oh, my.

52:23.160 --> 52:26.448
I think we need a new life plan,
Scooby-Don.

52:26.600 --> 52:28.125
Shaggy, look.

52:28.280 --> 52:32.251
A tin shack. It's a dream come true.

52:36.520 --> 52:40.206
Remember, Scoob, don't say anything
about me being a vampire.

52:40.360 --> 52:41.646
Okay.

52:42.760 --> 52:47.561
- Company? Come on in, cher. Hoo-hon!
SHAGGY: Whoa!

52:47.720 --> 52:51.042
Sit you down a spell
while I put on that gumbo.

52:51.200 --> 52:52.201
Gumbo?

52:52.360 --> 52:54.886
Like, man, our luck has changed, Scoob.

52:55.040 --> 52:57.407
My name's Tulie.

52:57.560 --> 52:58.925
That's not my real name, no.

52:59.080 --> 53:03.404
But that's what it say on the shack,
so I go with that. Hoo-hon!

53:08.920 --> 53:13.130
Hon! Look at that right there.
Now we cooking some kind of yeah.

53:13.280 --> 53:15.965
How come you live way out here
in the middle of nowhere?

53:16.120 --> 53:19.966
Well, if you must know, I'm on the run.

53:20.120 --> 53:22.441
- From what?
- Vampires!

53:22.600 --> 53:24.921
Ooh, I hate them, me.

53:25.080 --> 53:29.961
And if I ever catch me one,
I'm going to grind his bones for stew.

53:30.120 --> 53:31.884
Maybe we should be going.

53:32.040 --> 53:33.724
Stay right there.

53:33.880 --> 53:35.723
It's gumbo time.

53:37.320 --> 53:38.810
SCOOBY:
Ah.

53:41.400 --> 53:44.131
Well, I wasn't always a crazy old hermit.

53:44.280 --> 53:48.524
I used to be a handsome inventor
of fantastical devices.

53:48.680 --> 53:50.762
Oh, yeah? What'd you invent?

53:50.920 --> 53:54.163
Gadgets, whatchamacallits, thingamajigs.
Stuff that go:

53:54.320 --> 53:56.243
Buzz, buzz, hoppity-hoppity, hoop!

53:56.400 --> 53:59.483
I had me a little shop over there
at Petit Chauve Sourie Ville...

53:59.640 --> 54:00.926
...where I sold things...

54:01.080 --> 54:06.530
...the most popular item being a hat
with two cup holders and along straw...

54:06.680 --> 54:10.765
...so you could have two soda pops
while you're watching that ball game.

54:10.920 --> 54:14.447
Like, wow, ha, ha,
you invented the drinky hat?

54:14.600 --> 54:15.886
[LAUGHS]

54:16.040 --> 54:18.361
No, but I sold them in the store.

54:18.520 --> 54:23.367
Ain't nobody ever bought my inventions
because, like I said, they mostly just went.

54:23.520 --> 54:25.124
Bleep, bleep, bloop, bloop,
hoop, hoop.

54:25.280 --> 54:29.001
But then I created
the greatest invention ever:

54:29.160 --> 54:31.561
Flying shoes.

54:31.720 --> 54:34.007
They're based on the same principle
as a hover boat.

54:34.160 --> 54:36.845
But the fans be pointed down
to lift you off the ground.

54:37.000 --> 54:38.525
Whoo-whoo-whoo! There you go.

54:38.680 --> 54:41.365
And I was all set to show them
to a big shoe company...

54:41.520 --> 54:45.491
...when a vampire attacked me
and stole the prototypes.

54:45.640 --> 54:48.484
Well, I filed me an insurance claim.

54:48.640 --> 54:51.723
But it turns out
they don't cover vampire attacks.

54:52.040 --> 54:53.121
Hoo-hon.

54:53.280 --> 54:54.441
That's awful.

54:54.600 --> 54:55.726
More, please.

54:55.880 --> 54:56.927
Me too.

54:57.080 --> 54:58.764
I was ruined, y'all.

54:58.920 --> 55:01.571
I've been living out here
in the swamp ever since.

55:01.720 --> 55:04.690
And that is why
I hates me them vampires.

55:04.840 --> 55:07.002
Like, how long ago did this happen?

55:07.160 --> 55:10.607
I don't know, long as
I've been growing these here whiskers.

55:10.760 --> 55:12.489
Maybe two, three weeks now.

55:12.640 --> 55:13.766
Oh, well, that's life.

55:13.920 --> 55:16.969
You know, sometime you lose everything
on account of vampires...

55:17.120 --> 55:18.645
...sometime you don't. Ha, ha.

55:18.800 --> 55:19.961
How y'all like the gumbo?

55:20.120 --> 55:21.326
Amazing.

55:21.480 --> 55:25.530
Amazing. Mm-mm-mm.

55:25.800 --> 55:26.926
Yeah.

55:27.080 --> 55:29.890
That's because of my special ingredient.
Heh.

55:30.040 --> 55:33.044
Leeches.
I likes to put them leech in the gumbo.

55:33.200 --> 55:36.044
Leech gumbo. Yum. That's good, yeah.

55:37.640 --> 55:39.369
[SHAGGY YELLS]

55:42.120 --> 55:44.202
BOTH:
Thanks for everything.

55:44.360 --> 55:47.250
Y'all come back anytime!

55:48.520 --> 55:50.124
[GRUNTING]

55:50.280 --> 55:51.281
[GUN COCKS]

55:51.440 --> 55:56.162
Look at this. The stolen jewels are part of
some sort of vampire wedding ceremony.

55:56.320 --> 55:58.288
VAN HELSING:
The vampire bonding ritual.

55:58.440 --> 56:02.570
According to legend, if the vampire
takes the soul of his mortal bride...

56:02.720 --> 56:04.961
...he'll gain unbridled power.

56:05.120 --> 56:07.805
VELMA: The ceremony must take place
upon the third moon...

56:07.960 --> 56:10.440
...following the Vampire's release
from captivity.

56:10.600 --> 56:11.840
That's tonight.

56:12.000 --> 56:14.731
If Valdronya succeeds,
he'll be unstoppable.

56:14.880 --> 56:17.326
Unstoppable? Not if I can help it.

56:17.480 --> 56:21.451
Maybe vampires were tough to catch
back in the day, but times have changed.

56:21.600 --> 56:24.843
There's a new breed of vampire hunter
on the scene: me.

56:25.000 --> 56:27.890
Vampire hunting
is serious business, Fred.

56:28.040 --> 56:30.771
You must be prepared for anything.

56:30.920 --> 56:32.809
Oh, I'm prepared, all right.

56:32.960 --> 56:34.246
[VELMA & VAN HELSING YELL]

56:41.240 --> 56:42.730
Gotta watch that hair trigger.

56:42.880 --> 56:44.006
Not so fast.

56:44.160 --> 56:45.446
The vampire has the jewels...

56:45.600 --> 56:48.490
...but he still needs one thing
for the wedding: a bride.

56:48.640 --> 56:50.722
Not just any bride.

56:50.880 --> 56:54.248
A mortal beauty, pure of heart.

56:54.480 --> 56:55.970
That could take a while to find.

56:56.120 --> 56:57.929
[PHONE RINGS]

56:58.080 --> 57:00.208
Hey, it's a text from Daphne.

57:00.360 --> 57:03.204
"Been kidnapped by vampire actors.
Help!."

57:03.360 --> 57:06.603
A mortal beauty, pure of heart.

57:07.080 --> 57:08.889
- Daphne.
- Jinkies.

57:09.040 --> 57:11.327
I knew those actors
were involved somehow.

57:11.480 --> 57:13.005
According to the book...

57:13.160 --> 57:18.405
...those who offer up the Vampire's bride
will be rewarded with immortality.

57:18.560 --> 57:21.769
That's a heck of a finder's fee.
Any idea where they'll take her?

57:21.920 --> 57:26.164
I saw a star chart in here pointing out
the precise coordinates of the ceremony.

57:26.320 --> 57:28.368
We could make a copy.

57:29.080 --> 57:31.367
- Or that.
- Let's move.

57:31.520 --> 57:36.526
If the wedding takes place, Daphne
will become the bride of the vampire.

57:37.480 --> 57:39.244
You know, I'm pure of heart.

57:39.400 --> 57:42.563
Does anyone ever think
of kidnapping me? No.

57:42.720 --> 57:44.643
Uh, Velma, focus.

57:45.720 --> 57:46.721
Sorry.

57:47.080 --> 57:51.881
Tonight we give Valdronya the king
his queen.

57:52.040 --> 57:57.649
And we shall be rewarded
with eternal life as real vampires.

57:57.800 --> 58:00.690
All hail Valdronya!

58:00.840 --> 58:01.841
[GRUNTING]

58:02.000 --> 58:04.048
Relax, Daphne.

58:04.200 --> 58:06.202
It's just your soul you're giving up.

58:06.360 --> 58:09.762
Easy for you to say.
You obviously never had one.

58:12.960 --> 58:13.961
We're close.

58:15.200 --> 58:18.249
Stop. Did you hear that? In the trees.

58:18.400 --> 58:20.243
[RUSTLING AND SQUAWKING]

58:23.680 --> 58:25.205
[BOTH GASP]

58:26.760 --> 58:29.161
Must have been my imagination.

58:30.760 --> 58:32.524
[YELLS]

58:32.680 --> 58:35.524
- Hang on.
- Save yourselves.

58:35.680 --> 58:37.284
[YELLS]

58:39.880 --> 58:40.961
SHAGGY:
Zoinks!

58:41.120 --> 58:43.327
I got something. Come on.

58:47.240 --> 58:50.403
- Shaggy?
- Nice shooting, Fred.

58:50.560 --> 58:53.166
Scooby, what are you guys doing
in the swamp?

58:53.320 --> 58:55.368
Yeah, don't you know
it's dangerous out here?

58:55.640 --> 58:57.927
- Clearly.
- Yeah.

58:58.440 --> 59:00.681
The calibration is still off.

59:00.840 --> 59:02.365
Let's get you down from there.

59:02.760 --> 59:05.969
Don't get too close, Velma.
I've been bitten by a vampire.

59:06.120 --> 59:08.691
I could turn bloodsucker any second.

59:08.840 --> 59:10.410
That's no bite. It's a splinter.

59:10.560 --> 59:12.130
[SHAGGY YELLS THEN THUDS]

59:12.280 --> 59:15.409
So I'm not gonna turn
into a bloodsucking weirdo?

59:15.720 --> 59:19.167
Bloodsucker? No.
Weirdo? We're too late for that.

59:21.720 --> 59:22.926
Fire in the hole.

59:24.360 --> 59:25.964
[ALL YELL]

59:26.440 --> 59:27.521
Still off.

59:27.680 --> 59:31.730
Maybe it's best if you set that thing
to net mode from now on.

59:37.880 --> 59:40.690
The appointed hour is near, my friends.

59:40.840 --> 59:45.721
And soon our efforts will be repaid
with immortality.

59:46.480 --> 59:48.847
A jewel for a jewel.

59:49.320 --> 59:51.322
[DAPHNE GRUNTS]

59:51.480 --> 59:53.084
You're such the charmer.

59:53.240 --> 59:55.641
You are so lucky to be chosen.

59:55.800 --> 59:59.247
I'm sure you'll find an evil vampire king
of your own one day.

59:59.400 --> 01:00:02.529
Let the wedding ceremony begin!

01:00:02.680 --> 01:00:04.603
[DRAMATIC ORCHESTRAL MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

01:00:05.960 --> 01:00:09.282
ACTORS [SINGING]:
<i>♪ Ah, ah, ah, ah</i>

01:00:09.440 --> 01:00:12.489
<i>♪ Ah, ah, ah, ah</i>

01:00:12.640 --> 01:00:18.602
<i>♪ Dearly beloved
We're gathered today</i>

01:00:19.000 --> 01:00:25.326
<i>♪ To praise the one called Daphne
And give her away</i>

01:00:26.280 --> 01:00:32.686
<i>♪ Linked and joined forever
She'll be by your side</i>

01:00:32.840 --> 01:00:39.405
<i>♪ Valdronya, we present you
Your vampire bride ♪</i>

01:00:40.240 --> 01:00:42.766
- Looks like we're in time for the wedding.
- Wedding?

01:00:42.920 --> 01:00:46.129
I wish someone had told us.
We don't even have a gift.

01:00:46.280 --> 01:00:48.044
I've got a gift right here.

01:00:48.200 --> 01:00:49.645
- Huh?
- I don't get it.

01:00:49.800 --> 01:00:52.280
He means we're gonna stop the wedding
from happening.

01:00:52.440 --> 01:00:53.771
My way sounded cooler.

01:00:53.920 --> 01:00:56.400
ACTORS [SINGING]:
<i>♪ Hear us now, Valdronya</i>

01:00:56.560 --> 01:00:59.962
<i>♪ And come to our side</i>

01:01:00.480 --> 01:01:07.090
<i>♪ The time has come for claiming
Your vampire bride</i>

01:01:07.240 --> 01:01:10.767
<i>♪ Ah, ah, ah, ah</i>

01:01:10.920 --> 01:01:14.811
<i>♪ Ah, ah, ah, ah ♪</i>

01:01:17.640 --> 01:01:20.849
Behold, the king has heard our call.

01:01:21.600 --> 01:01:23.887
This is it. Here he comes.

01:01:25.960 --> 01:01:27.564
[SNARLS]

01:01:28.360 --> 01:01:32.046
Bow down before your king.

01:01:34.120 --> 01:01:35.121
[GASPS]

01:01:35.640 --> 01:01:39.565
Excellent work, my little vampire-lings.

01:01:39.720 --> 01:01:43.725
[SINGING] <i>♪ Close your eyes
♪ And come to me</i>

01:01:43.880 --> 01:01:47.680
<i>♪ When you wake
♪ Then you shall be</i>

01:01:47.840 --> 01:01:53.609
<i>♪ Alive for all eternity
♪ With me</i>

01:01:53.760 --> 01:01:56.445
[ALL SINGING IN ANCIENT TONGUE]

01:02:00.920 --> 01:02:04.481
<i>♪ Dark of the moon and
beauty so bright</i>

01:02:04.640 --> 01:02:07.849
<i>♪ Spirits arise and
call to the night</i>

01:02:08.000 --> 01:02:11.686
<i>♪ From Earth to the stars
And all that's between</i>

01:02:11.840 --> 01:02:16.846
<i>♪ Beware and behold
the vampire queen ♪</i>

01:02:17.000 --> 01:02:18.570
[GRUNTING]

01:02:18.720 --> 01:02:20.961
A mortal beauty.

01:02:22.480 --> 01:02:24.687
Your queen.

01:02:25.960 --> 01:02:27.485
SHAGGY:
Hold it.

01:02:28.720 --> 01:02:32.520
Hi. Uh, mind if I get a picture
of the happy couple?

01:02:32.680 --> 01:02:34.762
[ROARS]

01:02:34.920 --> 01:02:36.684
That one's for the memory book.

01:02:36.840 --> 01:02:38.080
Ha, ha. Yikes!

01:02:38.360 --> 01:02:39.361
[SNARLING]

01:02:41.440 --> 01:02:43.044
[SHAGGY YELLS]

01:02:45.000 --> 01:02:46.923
[GRUNTS THEN PANTING]

01:02:47.680 --> 01:02:49.603
[YELLING]

01:03:03.240 --> 01:03:04.844
[GASPS]

01:03:07.760 --> 01:03:09.364
[GRUNTS]

01:03:10.400 --> 01:03:12.004
[SNARLING]

01:03:19.520 --> 01:03:20.521
[GASPS]

01:03:26.720 --> 01:03:28.529
[BOTH YELLING]

01:03:38.400 --> 01:03:39.890
Daphne, you okay?

01:03:40.840 --> 01:03:43.650
Ha, ha. Velma, you came to my wedding.

01:03:43.800 --> 01:03:48.010
Oh, don't cry, Velma.
You won't always be a bridesmaid.

01:03:48.160 --> 01:03:49.571
I'm not crying.

01:03:49.720 --> 01:03:52.485
Valdronya's using gas
to hypnotize everyone.

01:03:52.640 --> 01:03:53.641
[SCOFFS]

01:03:53.800 --> 01:03:55.962
Whatever you've gotta tell yourself.
Ha, ha.

01:03:57.040 --> 01:03:59.805
SHAGGY:
Like, that is one unhappy groom.

01:03:59.960 --> 01:04:01.564
[SNARLS]

01:04:04.440 --> 01:04:06.124
[STAKE GUN BEEPING]

01:04:07.560 --> 01:04:10.689
Come on. I must have gotten water
in the compressor.

01:04:10.840 --> 01:04:13.889
Keep him busy while I fix this thing.

01:04:14.600 --> 01:04:16.841
- Aah!
- Dead end!

01:04:17.800 --> 01:04:19.723
Whoa!

01:04:21.160 --> 01:04:23.049
In more ways than one!

01:04:23.520 --> 01:04:25.170
[SNARLS]

01:04:25.320 --> 01:04:27.368
[LAUGHING]

01:04:32.520 --> 01:04:33.806
Yipe!

01:04:33.960 --> 01:04:35.724
[BOTH GRUNTING]

01:04:35.880 --> 01:04:37.086
Ha-ha-ha. Hm?

01:04:37.240 --> 01:04:39.288
DAPHNE:
Ahem. Here's your stupid amulet.

01:04:39.440 --> 01:04:40.441
[SNARLS]

01:04:40.600 --> 01:04:42.602
Nice shot.

01:04:42.760 --> 01:04:44.205
- He-yah!
- Unh!

01:04:44.640 --> 01:04:47.120
Actually, Velma,
I kind of wanted to keep that.

01:04:47.280 --> 01:04:48.281
Sorry.

01:04:48.680 --> 01:04:53.004
I'll make you all my vampire servants.

01:04:54.640 --> 01:04:56.563
[VALDRONYA YELLS]

01:04:56.840 --> 01:04:58.444
[ALL COUGHING]

01:05:08.040 --> 01:05:09.644
[GRUNTS]

01:05:19.080 --> 01:05:22.289
I'd say you're looking at a net loss.

01:05:24.040 --> 01:05:26.281
I think I'll raise the stakes.

01:05:27.400 --> 01:05:28.845
[GROANS]

01:05:29.480 --> 01:05:32.370
Let's see who's under that mask.

01:05:32.520 --> 01:05:36.889
Like I've been saying all along,
there's no such thing as real vampires.

01:05:37.040 --> 01:05:39.691
Right, Mr. Van Helsing?

01:05:39.840 --> 01:05:41.649
ALL:
Van Helsing?

01:05:42.080 --> 01:05:43.570
But why?

01:05:43.720 --> 01:05:46.121
He was trying to save
Petit Chauve Souris Ville...

01:05:46.280 --> 01:05:48.886
...by staging a series
of real live vampire events.

01:05:49.040 --> 01:05:52.283
Events tied to his latest book,
The <i>Bride</i> of the Vampire...

01:05:52.440 --> 01:05:54.727
...which I actually read. It's not bad.

01:05:54.880 --> 01:05:56.530
You really liked it?

01:05:56.680 --> 01:05:59.047
I said it's not bad. Don't push it.

01:05:59.200 --> 01:06:03.410
So by creating a real vampire legend,
he'd get tourists year-round.

01:06:03.560 --> 01:06:04.971
And sell books.

01:06:05.120 --> 01:06:06.121
[SIGHS]

01:06:06.280 --> 01:06:07.361
It's true.

01:06:07.520 --> 01:06:10.763
I wanted to put the Van Helsing name
back on the map.

01:06:10.920 --> 01:06:13.651
I thought once word spread
of the ceremony...

01:06:13.800 --> 01:06:16.041
...tourists would flock here
to see the place...

01:06:16.200 --> 01:06:19.886
...where a real live vampire
wedding ritual had happened.

01:06:20.200 --> 01:06:22.771
Then I would no longer need
Lita Rutland...

01:06:22.920 --> 01:06:26.641
...and her schlocky Vampire Palooza
to make ends meet.

01:06:26.800 --> 01:06:28.484
And what about the actors?

01:06:28.640 --> 01:06:30.085
VELMA:
Merely pawns in his game.

01:06:30.240 --> 01:06:33.961
<i>They were so devoted to the vampire
way of life, they were easily duped.</i>

01:06:34.120 --> 01:06:38.125
<i>When Valdronya first appeared, they really
thought their ritual had conjured him up.</i>

01:06:38.280 --> 01:06:41.409
Van Helsing used their intense belief
in vampires against them.

01:06:41.560 --> 01:06:45.884
But Van Helsing was in the audience when
Valdronya materialized in the theater.

01:06:46.040 --> 01:06:48.725
DAPHNE:
<i>He used a laser projector for that.</i>

01:06:48.880 --> 01:06:52.089
VELMA: <i>I'd wager he planted
similar projectors in the museum...</i>

01:06:52.240 --> 01:06:54.925
<i>...to give the illusion of the vampire
in the glass coffin.</i>

01:06:55.080 --> 01:06:58.607
<i>Security cameras rewired for
special effects would explain a lot...</i>

01:06:58.760 --> 01:07:03.561
<i>...including why there was no surveillance
footage of Valdronya's supposed escape.</i>

01:07:03.720 --> 01:07:07.327
<i>When Daphne tore off a piece of modern
fabric from Valdronya's cloak...</i>

01:07:07.480 --> 01:07:10.768
<i>...Mr. Van Helsing must've feared the
threads of his plot were unraveling...</i>

01:07:10.920 --> 01:07:11.967
<i>...so to speak.</i>

01:07:12.120 --> 01:07:13.167
<i>Looking at it now...</i>

01:07:13.320 --> 01:07:17.769
<i>...I suspect he passed off ancient
fabric from his museum as a cover-up.</i>

01:07:17.920 --> 01:07:21.811
He staged his own demise in the swamp
using this.

01:07:21.960 --> 01:07:24.327
BOTH:
Aah! Vampires!

01:07:24.480 --> 01:07:27.882
No, a simple mechanical device
he planted in the marsh.

01:07:28.240 --> 01:07:29.765
Probably a prop from the theater.

01:07:29.920 --> 01:07:31.729
So when he was kicking and flailing...

01:07:31.880 --> 01:07:34.770
He was actually triggering it.

01:07:35.800 --> 01:07:38.280
But, like,
how did he hypnotize everyone?

01:07:39.280 --> 01:07:40.725
Knockout gas.

01:07:40.880 --> 01:07:42.166
<i>No one knew what hit them.</i>

01:07:42.320 --> 01:07:44.846
<i>But when they awoke,
they remembered seeing Valdronya...</i>

01:07:45.000 --> 01:07:47.401
<i>...and thought he'd mesmerized them.</i>

01:07:50.880 --> 01:07:52.803
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

01:07:53.600 --> 01:07:55.967
By gassing everyone at the wedding,
he'd slip away...

01:07:56.120 --> 01:07:59.522
...but leave eyewitnesses to tell the
tale of Valdronya and his bride.

01:07:59.680 --> 01:08:03.321
The actors already lived like vampires,
so they could just go on like that...

01:08:03.480 --> 01:08:05.289
...thinking they were actually immortal.

01:08:05.440 --> 01:08:08.171
You've really thought of everything.

01:08:08.320 --> 01:08:09.924
Eh, it's what we do.

01:08:14.840 --> 01:08:18.606
Daphne, I... I'm sorry
for putting you through all this.

01:08:18.760 --> 01:08:22.651
Well, it's not every day a girl is kidnapped
to be an ancient Vampire's bride.

01:08:22.800 --> 01:08:24.848
In a strange way, I'm flattered.

01:08:25.200 --> 01:08:29.330
Really? Maybe after I get out of prison,
we could grab a coffee and...

01:08:29.479 --> 01:08:31.926
Heh. Not on your life, bat boy.

01:08:32.080 --> 01:08:33.366
I don't date actors.

01:08:33.520 --> 01:08:35.283
Move along, fella.

01:08:36.040 --> 01:08:38.725
Like, there's one thing
about this whole plan I don't get.

01:08:38.880 --> 01:08:40.803
Why'd Van Helsing need us?

01:08:40.960 --> 01:08:42.849
You were my credible witnesses.

01:08:43.000 --> 01:08:47.085
It's one thing to have a bunch of
weirdo vampire-reenactment nuts...

01:08:47.240 --> 01:08:48.685
...spreading my tale.

01:08:48.840 --> 01:08:50.763
Quite another
when the story is recounted...

01:08:50.920 --> 01:08:54.287
...by respected monster hunters
such as yourselves.

01:08:54.840 --> 01:08:56.205
We're respected?

01:08:56.359 --> 01:08:59.250
My family's legacy
would have been restored.

01:08:59.600 --> 01:09:02.251
Not to mention,
you would have sold loads of books.

01:09:03.000 --> 01:09:04.843
That too.

01:09:05.960 --> 01:09:07.404
[SIGHS]

01:09:08.040 --> 01:09:11.840
Wow, like, that is one elaborate plan.

01:09:12.000 --> 01:09:14.765
And I would have gotten away with it,
if not for you meddling...

01:09:14.920 --> 01:09:17.685
Let's go, Van Helsing.

01:09:19.640 --> 01:09:22.211
Well, gang,
it looks like another mystery is solved.

